The paper deals with learning-based image translation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The proposed model and training scheme involve the use of multiple components, which suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) component. The paper also mentions the use of a dataset of paintings, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper deals with image translation, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
